          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Overview</span><h2>What Are Large Cap Funds?</h2></div>
            <p>Large cap mutual funds are equity funds that invest a minimum of 80% of their corpus in stocks of the top 100 companies by market capitalization, as per SEBI's categorization norms. These companies — including Reliance Industries, TCS, HDFC Bank, Infosys, and ITC — are well-established market leaders with proven track records, strong financials, and high liquidity.</p>
            <p>Large cap funds are considered the most stable category within equity mutual funds. While they may not deliver the explosive returns of mid or small cap funds, they offer consistent performance with lower drawdowns during market corrections. Over the past decade, top large cap funds have delivered annualized returns of 12%–14%, significantly outperforming inflation and fixed-income instruments.</p>
            <p>These funds are ideal as a core equity allocation for first-time equity investors, retirees looking for growth with relatively lower risk, and anyone with a 5+ year investment horizon who wants exposure to India's blue-chip companies without the volatility of smaller companies.</p>
          </div>

