          <div class="content-section">
            <div class="section-header"><span class="section-tag">Benefits</span><h2>Why Invest in Large Cap Funds?</h2></div>
            <ul class="feature-list">
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Invest in India's Top Companies</strong><p>Large cap funds give you ownership in the country's largest, most profitable companies — household names that dominate their industries. These companies have strong moats, proven business models, and access to capital that enables sustained growth.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Lower Volatility vs Mid/Small Caps</strong><p>Large cap stocks typically fall less during market corrections and recover faster. During the 2020 crash, large cap funds fell 25%–30% vs 35%–45% for small caps. This stability makes them suitable for investors with moderate risk tolerance.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Consistent Long-Term Returns</strong><p>Over 10+ year periods, large cap funds have consistently delivered 12%–14% CAGR, significantly beating inflation (5%–6%) and fixed deposits (6%–7%). ₹10,000/month SIP for 10 years at 13% CAGR grows to approximately ₹24.5 lakh (₹12 lakh invested).</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>High Liquidity & Transparency</strong><p>Large cap stocks are the most liquid on exchanges with high daily trading volumes. Fund portfolios are disclosed monthly, and NAV is calculated daily. You can redeem your investment on any business day.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Ideal Core Portfolio Holding</strong><p>Financial advisors recommend large cap funds as the "core" of any equity portfolio (50%–70% of equity allocation). They provide stable, reliable growth while satellite allocations to mid/small caps can add alpha.</p></div></li>
              <li><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i><div><strong>Best Entry Point for Equity Beginners</strong><p>If you're new to equity investing, large cap funds are the recommended starting point. Their lower volatility and steady performance help build confidence in equity markets before venturing into riskier categories.</p></div></li>
            </ul>
          </div>

